President Donald Trump sat down with lawmakers at the White House Wednesday afternoon to discuss gun policy in the wake of the shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Florida  and Trump appeared to enthusiastically endorse several gun control measures, including a bipartisan gun control bill that failed to pass the Senate during Barack Obamas presidency.

It was a surprising scene, but its not yet clear if Trumps words will translate into policy. Below is a full rush transcript of the meeting at the White House:

We have to do something about it. We have to act.

